1
00:00:02,680 --> 00:00:10,580
Namo dasa bhagavato arahato samasambuddhasa

2
00:00:11,387 --> 00:00:34,813
Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambodasa Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambodasa Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-awakened one.

3
00:00:39,906 --> 00:00:40,468
Very good.

4
00:00:41,770 --> 00:00:49,020
So, last week we tackled this very cryptic saying from the Buddha, this very cryptic teaching.

5
00:00:49,039 --> 00:00:52,985
He couldn't have reduced his teaching any further, I don't think.

6
00:00:53,987 --> 00:00:56,631
It was about all Bahir of the Barcloth.

7
00:00:56,651 --> 00:01:04,783
So, I said that this week we would actually read the discourse and revise what we said, because it's quite difficult, really.

8
00:01:05,557 --> 00:01:14,909
So the collection that this belongs to, by the way, is called the Udana, U-D-A-N-A.

9
00:01:15,269 --> 00:01:20,936
I'll try to remember to put it in the chat box for you, which you can buy as a little booklet.

10
00:01:21,037 --> 00:01:22,840
It's translated by John Ireland.

11
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:25,283
So that's where this translation comes from.

12
00:01:26,424 --> 00:01:28,126
Okay, the Bahia Sutta.

13
00:01:28,406 --> 00:01:29,808
This is about Bahia.

14
00:01:30,362 --> 00:01:31,545
Thus have I heard.

15
00:01:32,006 --> 00:01:44,126
At one time the Lord was staying near Sābhati in the Jeta Wood at Anathipindika's monastery, and at that time Vaheera the Barcloth was living by the seashore at Suparaka.

16
00:01:44,146 --> 00:01:49,114
He was respected, revered, honoured, venerated and given homage.

17
00:01:49,194 --> 00:01:54,427
and was one who obtained the requisites of robes, alms, food, lodging and medicines.

18
00:01:55,170 --> 00:02:03,171
We said last week that he was probably a follower of a particular Brahmin sect, depending on the Upanishads.

19
00:02:03,251 --> 00:02:06,920
and that their signature was wearing bark cloth.

20
00:02:07,421 --> 00:02:23,133
But here it's really talking about the myth that arose from him whereby he gets shipwrecked and he must have had a Damascene moment out at sea because when he lands he doesn't want to be a merchant anymore.

21
00:02:23,114 --> 00:02:29,784
He wants to be a samana, an ascetic, and he gains the respect of everybody.

22
00:02:30,406 --> 00:02:37,697
And these four requisites, robes, arms, food, lodging, and medicines, that's the requisites of the Buddhist order.

23
00:02:38,498 --> 00:02:39,920
It's really basic, isn't it?

24
00:02:40,061 --> 00:02:41,644
That's all you need to live.

25
00:02:41,963 --> 00:02:48,835
There's something to wear, something to eat, a roof over your head, and medicine when you're sick.

26
00:02:51,058 --> 00:02:56,048
So now, while he was in seclusion, this reflection arose in the mind of Bahir of the Barcloth.

27
00:02:56,830 --> 00:03:03,040
Am I one of those in the world who are Arahats and who have entered the path of Arahatship?

28
00:03:03,061 --> 00:03:05,906
And the word Arahat is an honorific, really.

29
00:03:05,925 --> 00:03:11,235
It's the blessed one or the holy one or something like that.

30
00:03:11,977 --> 00:03:15,143
But of course, it's given to somebody who's completed the path.

31
00:03:16,050 --> 00:03:23,221
Then a Devata, who was a former blood relation of Bahir of the Barcloth, understood this reflection in his mind.

32
00:03:23,882 --> 00:03:33,796
Being compassionate and wishing to benefit him, she approached Bahir and said, You, Bahir, are neither an Arahat, nor have you entered the path to Arahatship.

33
00:03:34,457 --> 00:03:41,227
You do not follow that practice whereby you could be an Arahat or enter the path of Arahatship.

34
00:03:41,968 --> 00:03:43,090
That's a bit crushing, isn't it?

35
00:03:43,330 --> 00:03:45,753
I mean, a poor man's living.

36
00:03:45,734 --> 00:04:09,447
doing the best he can and this devatas told him he's wasting his time then he asks in the world including the devas all the gods who are the arahants and who have entered the path of arahantship this there is bahia in a far country a town called savati there the lord now lives who is an arahat and fully enlightened one

37
00:04:09,764 --> 00:04:35,416
that lord bahia is indeed an arahat and he teaches the dharma for the realization of arahatship then by here the back cloth profoundly stirred by the words of that devata then and there departed for from suparaka stopping only one night everywhere along the way he went to sabati where the lord was staying at the jetta wood at anati pindika's monastery

38
00:04:36,206 --> 00:04:41,713
At that time, a number of bhikkhus were walking up and down, doing walking meditation in the open air.

39
00:04:41,754 --> 00:04:50,083
Then Bahir the Barcloth approached those bhikkhus and said, Where, revered sirs, is the Lord now living, the Arahat, the fully enlightened one?

40
00:04:51,043 --> 00:04:54,408
We wish to see the Lord who is an Arahat, the fully enlightened one.

41
00:04:55,269 --> 00:04:59,194
The Lord, Bahir, has gone on arms round among the houses.

42
00:04:59,781 --> 00:05:02,185
Then Bahiya hurriedly left the Jeta Grove.

43
00:05:02,446 --> 00:05:07,052
Entering Sabati, he saw the Lord walking for alms food in Sabati.

44
00:05:08,095 --> 00:05:22,478
Pleasing, lovely to see, with calm senses and tranquil mind, attained to perfect poise and calm, controlled, a perfected one, watchful with restrained senses.

45
00:05:23,259 --> 00:05:26,463
So that's a classic trope describing the Buddha.

46
00:05:27,810 --> 00:05:39,928
On seeing the Lord, he approached, fell down with his head at the Lord's feet and said, Teach me Dharma, Lord, teach me Dharma, Sugata, so that it will be for my good and the happiness for a long time.

47
00:05:40,711 --> 00:05:45,377
This Sugata translates literally as well gone.

48
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:51,507
It obviously means somebody who's transcended, gone to Nibbana.

49
00:05:53,392 --> 00:05:58,862
Upon being spoken to thus, the Lord said to Bahir of the Barcloth, It is an unsuitable time, Bahir.

50
00:05:59,343 --> 00:06:01,545
We have entered among the houses for alms-food.

51
00:06:02,427 --> 00:06:09,899
A second time Bahir said to the Lord, It is difficult to know, for certain, revered sir, how long the Lord will live.

52
00:06:09,879 --> 00:06:11,341
And how long I will live?

53
00:06:11,663 --> 00:06:19,132
Teach me, Dharma Lord, teach me, Dharma Sugata, so that it will be for my good and happiness for a long time.

54
00:06:19,874 --> 00:06:24,600
A second time the Lord said to Bahir, it is an unsuitable time, Bahir.

55
00:06:24,661 --> 00:06:27,264
We have entered among the houses for alms food.

56
00:06:28,476 --> 00:06:30,000
But Bahir wouldn't give up, you see.

57
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:38,156
A third time Bahir said to the Lord, it is difficult to know for certain, revered sir, how long the Lord will live and how long I will live.

58
00:06:38,216 --> 00:06:39,579
Teach me Dharma, Lord.

59
00:06:39,660 --> 00:06:46,333
Teach me Dharma, Sugata, so that it will be for my good and happiness for a long time.

60
00:06:46,312 --> 00:06:50,040
Now, this is one of these things that perhaps was part of the age.

61
00:06:50,581 --> 00:06:57,072
You could ask three times, and if the answer was still no, there was no point in asking again.

62
00:06:57,593 --> 00:07:03,343
So this time the Buddha took pity on Poro Bahia, and he said this,

63
00:07:03,322 --> 00:07:27,762
here in bahia you should train yourself thus in the scene will be merely what is seen in the herd will be merely what is heard in the sensed will be merely what is sensed in the cognized will be merely what is cognized in this way you should train yourself by here okay so now this is referring directly to our vipassana practice

64
00:07:28,619 --> 00:07:35,692
So the Buddha categorizes consciousnesses according to the sense base.

65
00:07:36,213 --> 00:07:44,990
So you have eye consciousness, ear consciousness, nose, taste, and body consciousness.

66
00:07:45,358 --> 00:07:46,740
the mind consciousness.

67
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:53,009
So what the mind is aware of, of course, is the internal life, the interior life of emotions and thoughts.

68
00:07:53,690 --> 00:08:00,120
So these are your six bases, and it's upon these bases that consciousness arises.

69
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:04,105
Okay.

70
00:08:04,747 --> 00:08:11,315
So he says, so when, Bahir, when you are in the scene, when for you in the scene,

71
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:28,069
is merely what is seen, in the heard is merely what is heard, in the sensed, which means smelling and tasting, in the sensed will be merely what is sensed, in the cognized is merely what is cognized, then, Bahir, you will not be with that.

72
00:08:29,351 --> 00:08:33,236
When, Bahir, you are not with that, you will not be in that.

73
00:08:33,975 --> 00:08:58,278
when by here you are not in that then by here you will be neither here nor beyond nor in between the two just this is the end of suffering now he's pointing he's saying to bahia you will not be in that now remember if we go back to this um uh this upanishad uh it's talking about the the the uh

74
00:08:59,288 --> 00:09:09,697
The unknown knower is always pointing to somebody, the one who understands, the censor, etc., etc.

75
00:09:10,437 --> 00:09:18,024
So now what Bahiyya seems to have been doing is looking for this knower, and of course he's not finding it.

76
00:09:18,625 --> 00:09:29,193
So the Buddha tries to avert him from that and draw him down to the level where he's just experiencing things without the sense of I.

77
00:09:29,984 --> 00:09:59,687
so at that very base level there's always an a sense base and a sense base is has some object that it's sensing okay so obviously you know if you've got eyes and you're looking then you'll see something like for instance now you see me now those two then have to have some way of relating that information

78
00:10:00,072 --> 00:10:03,255
onto something that can be seen, can be known.

79
00:10:03,796 --> 00:10:05,557
And that's what consciousness is.

80
00:10:05,618 --> 00:10:08,861
That's the candor consciousness, the consciousness of the aggregates.

81
00:10:09,783 --> 00:10:13,326
All these consciousness are dependent on a sense base.

82
00:10:15,009 --> 00:10:22,337
Now, in our meditation, you see, what we're trying to do is to get down to that level where there isn't an I.

83
00:10:22,977 --> 00:10:26,282
What happens normally is we see something,

84
00:10:27,325 --> 00:10:28,847
We don't see it as it is.

85
00:10:29,207 --> 00:10:34,157
We see it within a category, which is our conceptual understanding.

86
00:10:35,097 --> 00:10:41,249
So when I see, for instance, an apple, I don't see that apple as something distinct and spare.

87
00:10:41,710 --> 00:10:45,216
I see it within my concepts of what apples are.

88
00:10:45,196 --> 00:11:14,815
and depending on that concept i'll be able to say to myself well this is a sweet apple or it's not so sweet and then of course there's i like sweet apples i don't like unsweet apples and then once you've said that you have a relationship with it i want a sweet apple or simply want a sweet apple and then you get the i want a sweet apple now what he's asking by here to do is to cut through that whole

89
00:11:15,267 --> 00:11:21,572
mentation dependent on a delusion of an eye and get down to basics.

90
00:11:22,754 --> 00:11:32,543
And once he does that, of course, he recognizes that there is something which is aware of what's on that screen of consciousness.

91
00:11:33,644 --> 00:11:42,472
And that separation allows him to make the insight of what he really is before he becomes an eye.

92
00:11:43,852 --> 00:12:12,696
i hope that hasn't confused you completely right it's quite the teaching is quite difficult so um when he says you are not with that in other words you don't identify with the object right by way of conceptual understanding the apple right you don't you're not in that you're not identifying with the sense base right the taste the sense of taste

93
00:12:13,418 --> 00:12:25,494
And when you don't identify with that, what comes up on the screen is pure, without the manipulation, the distortion of liking, not liking, wanting, not wanting.

94
00:12:27,155 --> 00:12:34,865
And that's when we're able to see that there is something which is distinct from everything that we're experiencing.

95
00:12:35,647 --> 00:12:38,030
And that's the process of awakening.

96
00:12:38,490 --> 00:12:39,072
That's what it is.

97
00:12:40,232 --> 00:12:55,102
So then he says, now through this brief dharma teaching of the Lord, the mind of Bahir the Bakloth was immediately free from the taints without grasping.

98
00:12:55,352 --> 00:12:59,619
Then the Lord, having instructed Bahir with this brief instruction, went away.

99
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:04,986
So now this is the point, this is what happens when we become fully liberated.

100
00:13:05,307 --> 00:13:07,090
We are free from the taints.

101
00:13:07,590 --> 00:13:16,261
Now the word is asawa, and there is in that word the meaning of the word su, which means to flow.

102
00:13:17,024 --> 00:13:19,706
So it's like the corruptions are flowing out of us.

103
00:13:20,107 --> 00:13:23,773
Sometimes they're called inflows, sometimes outflows.

104
00:13:23,753 --> 00:13:52,258
and they are the basic um delusions that are affecting our lives for the worse of course so the first one is the taint craving for sensual pleasure right craving percentual pleasure the second one is the craving for existence in other words always becoming right that's why you know anytime death approaches us we we panic

105
00:13:52,998 --> 00:13:56,543
So we want to continue from moment after moment.

106
00:13:56,845 --> 00:13:58,126
And we want to be somebody.

107
00:13:58,427 --> 00:14:00,552
We're always redefining ourselves.

108
00:14:01,734 --> 00:14:09,167
And finally, of course, the taint of ignorance, which, of course, is not understanding the way things really are.

109
00:14:09,847 --> 00:14:12,111
So he's freed of all that.

110
00:14:12,552 --> 00:14:15,798
And because he's freed of all that, he's come to the end of suffering.

111
00:14:17,585 --> 00:14:24,945
So then, of course, not long after the Lord's departure, a cow with a young calf attacked Bahia of the Barcloth and killed him.

112
00:14:26,072 --> 00:14:38,510
When the Lord, having walked for alms food in Sarvati, was returning from alms-room with a number of bhikkhus, on departing from the town, he saw that bhikkhu, that Bahir of the bark cloth, had died.

113
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:49,326
Seeing this, he said to the bhikkhus, Bhikkhus, take Bahir's body, put it on a litter, carry it away and burn it, and make a stupa for it.

114
00:14:49,748 --> 00:14:52,772
Your companion in the holy life has died.

115
00:14:53,292 --> 00:14:56,017
So a stupa would be a mound in those days, that's all.

116
00:14:56,979 --> 00:15:00,264
Very well, revered sir, the bhikkhus replied to the Lord.

117
00:15:00,745 --> 00:15:06,897
Taking Bahiya's body, they put it on a litter, carried it away and burnt it, and made a stupa for it.

118
00:15:08,519 --> 00:15:13,207
Then they went to the Lord, prostrated themselves, and sat down to one side.

119
00:15:14,486 --> 00:15:21,393
Sitting there, those bhikkhus said to the Lord, Bahir's body has been burnt, revered sir, and a stupa has been made for it.

120
00:15:22,114 --> 00:15:23,615
What is his destiny?

121
00:15:23,835 --> 00:15:26,638
What is his future birth?

122
00:15:26,658 --> 00:15:30,221
Bhikkhus, Bahir of the Barcloth was a wise man.

123
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:37,267
He practiced according to the Dharma and did not trouble me by disputing about Dharma.

124
00:15:38,028 --> 00:15:42,991
Bhikkhus, Bahir of the Barcloth has attained final nibbana.

125
00:15:44,474 --> 00:15:48,844
Now, I love the way this little phrase has been put in there.

126
00:15:49,565 --> 00:15:53,354
So, did not trouble me by disputing about Dharma.

127
00:15:53,774 --> 00:16:00,068
So he was constantly hassled by people, you know, questioning what he understood, what he taught.

128
00:16:00,671 --> 00:16:04,018
I find that a lovely little phrase to tell you something about the Buddha's life.

129
00:16:06,125 --> 00:16:11,653
Then on realizing this significance, the Lord uttered on that occasion this inspired utterance.

130
00:16:11,793 --> 00:16:16,499
Okay, so this is where he's stating what nirvana is, okay?

131
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:28,034
Where neither water, nor yet earth, nor fire, nor air, find a foothold, gain a foothold.

132
00:16:28,054 --> 00:16:35,625
There gleam no stars, no sun sheds light, there shines no moon.

133
00:16:36,212 --> 00:17:02,101
yet there no darkness reigns okay so the first of course is our physicality which of course includes the whole psychophysical organism where neither water these are the four great elements water earth fire and air and then the outer world the material world that we live in

134
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:09,869
Gleam no stars, no sun sheds lights, there shines no moon, yet no darkness reigns.

135
00:17:11,132 --> 00:17:19,563
Now, I was listening to a talk by Bhikkhu Bodhi, in which he was asked, what is the understanding of this Nirvana, you see?

136
00:17:20,223 --> 00:17:23,669
And he said that in the Theravada Buddhism, there were two understandings.

137
00:17:24,410 --> 00:17:26,132
The first one was that

138
00:17:26,617 --> 00:17:37,915
When you've finally purified your heart and it's time to become liberated, the five khandhas, the psycho-physical organism, comes to an end, and that's it.

139
00:17:38,797 --> 00:17:49,233
Now, I know people who believe that, that that's what the Buddha's teaching, and I cannot, I just cannot know the difference between that and annihilation.

140
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:54,904
And the Buddha, often in the discourses, says he is not teaching annihilation.

141
00:17:55,145 --> 00:18:01,152
He says the only things that are annihilated are greed, hatred and delusion.

142
00:18:02,634 --> 00:18:15,508
And then Bhikkhu Bodhi says the second reason, the second understanding, which is the traditional understanding, is that when the psychophysical organism, the five khandhas, come to an end,

143
00:18:16,146 --> 00:18:25,497
There is a transcendent experience, and that's what this, yet there no darkness reigns, is pointing to.

144
00:18:26,618 --> 00:18:38,290
And if you actually get that book, the Udana, the inspired verses of the Buddha, you'll see that there's a whole section on Nibbāna, and they're all basically pointing to the same thing.

145
00:18:41,694 --> 00:18:45,259
Dogen Zenji, actually, the great Zen master,

146
00:18:45,829 --> 00:18:58,674
talked about his moment of liberation by saying the body and mind fell away right the body and mind fell away that's another way of stating it

147
00:18:59,481 --> 00:19:16,680
So then he goes on, when a sage, a Brahmin, has come to know this for himself through his own wise experience, insight experience, then he is freed from form and formless, freed from pleasure and from pain.

148
00:19:16,921 --> 00:19:18,622
In other words, he's gone beyond.

149
00:19:18,742 --> 00:19:27,632
He's gone beyond all the amazing stuff you can get from absorption techniques, and he's gone beyond all that we can...

150
00:19:27,612 --> 00:19:56,556
experience pleasure or pain from our physicality so he's always pointing to something which is beyond now he doesn't want to call it he doesn't want to give it a name he doesn't want to substantiate it because then you end up like bahia completely confused looking for your soul by looking for your eternal self and that's why he's constantly pointing to it but not giving it a name of course in later buddhism

151
00:19:57,008 --> 00:20:06,941
in Mahayana Buddhism, they began talking about it as the Dharmakaya, the body of the truth, sometimes Buddha nature.

152
00:20:08,682 --> 00:20:13,229
This inspired utterance was spoken by the Lord also.

153
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,951
So did I hear.

154
00:20:19,016 --> 00:20:19,557
Very good.

155
00:20:19,596 --> 00:20:26,526
Well, as usual, I can only hope my words have been of some assistance, that they have not caused confusion.

156
00:20:27,181 --> 00:20:35,267
and that by your careful investigation you will be liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later.

